<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="50" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,700,938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. M. Hern. A. Branchlet" authorityYear="2019" box="[136,367,700,721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis box="[136,367,700,721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Calliandra estebanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="L'Heritier (1788: 30) Bentham (1840: 139)" authorityName="L'Heritier (1788: 30) Bentham" authorityYear="1840" box="[557,1103,700,722]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[557,694,700,721]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">C. grandiflora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="L'Heritier, Ch. L." box="[698,897,700,722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" refId="ref2979" refString="L'Heritier, Ch. L. (1788 [1789]) Sertum Anglicum. Paris, p. 30, pl. 42 [plate not published]" type="book" year="1788">L’Héritier (1788: 30)</bibRefCitation>
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[901,1103,700,722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="127 - 146" refId="ref2782" refString="Bentham, G. (1840) Contributions towards a flora of South America. VI. Enumeration of plants collected by Mr. Schomburck in British Guiana. Journal of Botany (Hooker) 2 (11): 127 - 146." type="journal article" year="1840">Bentham (1840: 139)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from which it could be distinguished by having flowers with longer (
<quantity box="[488,577,736,757]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="cm" value="1.55" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.1">1.1–2 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[615,723,736,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="cm" value="0.8999999999999999" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.6">0.6–1.2 cm</quantity>
) peduncles, shorter (
<quantity box="[920,1000,736,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[1038,1130,736,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10 mm</quantity>
) pedicels, and larger calyces (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[267,349,772,793]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
) and corollas (
<quantity box="[493,597,772,794]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="10.0">10–16 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity box="[638,734,772,793]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.0">8–12 mm</quantity>
), prominently covered by a much denser white-sericeous (vs. white, black or ferruginous pilose) vestiture.
</paragraph>
