<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,984,2091]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,400,1920,1946]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. M. Hern. A. Branchlet" authorityYear="2019" box="[428,700,1920,1946]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis box="[428,700,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Calliandra estebanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly belongs to 
<emphasis box="[915,941,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">C.</emphasis>
ser. 
<taxonomicName box="[994,1122,1921,1946]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Racemosae">
<emphasis box="[994,1122,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Racemosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[1130,1371,1920,1946]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="82 - 112" refId="ref2826" refString="Bentham, G. (1844) Notes on Mimoseae, with a synopsis of species. London Journal of Botany 3: 82 - 112." type="journal article" year="1844">Bentham (1844: 111)</bibRefCitation>
, which includes eight Mexican and Central American microphyllidious species characterized by having terminal, efoliate pseudoracemose inflorescences, with the flowers grouped in capitula or umbels inserted in several nodes along elongated axis (
<bibRefCitation author="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M." box="[196,539,2028,2054]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3008" refString="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M. (1997) A revision of Calliandra series Racemosae (Leguminosae: Mimosoideae). Kew Bulletin 52 (1): 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4117840" type="journal article" year="1997">Macqueen &amp; Hernández 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Bentham’s 
<emphasis box="[686,712,2028,2054]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">C.</emphasis>
ser. 
<taxonomicName box="[764,892,2029,2054]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Racemosae">
<emphasis box="[764,892,2029,2054]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Racemosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, was sunk by 
<bibRefCitation author="Barneby, R. C." box="[1162,1451,2028,2054]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref2736" refString="Barneby, R. C. (1998) Silk tree, guanacaste, monkey's earring. A generic system for the synandrous Mimosaceae of the Americas. Part III. Calliandra. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 74: 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1998">Barneby (1998: 148–149)</bibRefCitation>
into 
<emphasis box="[189,215,2064,2090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">C.</emphasis>
ser. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1840" box="[272,395,2064,2090]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,395,2064,2090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Calliandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which includes 39 species grouped into two geographically congruent assemblages, one in 
<collectingCountry box="[136,207,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and the other in 
<collectingCountry box="[408,494,158,184]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Central America. Nonetheless, we consider 
<emphasis box="[1049,1075,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C.</emphasis>
ser. 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1258,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Racemosae">
<emphasis box="[1130,1258,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Racemosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an acceptable taxon to include a compact group of North and Central American species with racemose inflorescences and, thus, treat 
<taxonomicName box="[136,297,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanesis">
<emphasis box="[136,297,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. estebanesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
The precise taxonomic relationships of the new species are difficult to determine based on overall morphology. There are three species in 
<taxonomicName box="[441,749,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="series" series="Racemosae">
<emphasis box="[441,564,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Calliandra</emphasis>
ser. 
<emphasis box="[621,749,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Racemosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in western and northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1302,302,328]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, that may be superficially confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. M. Hern. A. Branchlet" authorityYear="2019" box="[451,626,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis box="[451,626,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. estebanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="S. Watson (1887: 410)" authorityName="S. Watson" authorityPageNumber="410" authorityYear="1887" box="[641,1026,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palmeri">
<emphasis box="[641,762,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. palmeri</emphasis>
S. 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, S." box="[800,1026,338,365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="396 - 481" refId="ref3265" refString="Watson, S. (1887) Contributions to American botany. XXI. Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences 22: 396 - 481. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25129875" type="journal article" year="1887">Watson (1887: 410)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="McVaugh (1987: 151 - 152) Macqueen &amp; Hernandez (1997: 40)" authorityName="McVaugh (1987: 151 - 152) Macqueen &amp; Hernandez" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedicellata">
<emphasis box="[1038,1254,338,365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. longipedicellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McVaugh, R." pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="791" refId="ref3057" refString="McVaugh, R. (1987) Leguminosae. In: Anderson, W. R. (Ed.) Flora Novo-Galiciana. A descriptive account of the vascular plants of western Mexico. Vol. 5. pp. 791." type="journal article" year="1987">McVaugh (1987: 151–152)</bibRefCitation>
<bibRefCitation author="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M." box="[253,661,374,401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3008" refString="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M. (1997) A revision of Calliandra series Racemosae (Leguminosae: Mimosoideae). Kew Bulletin 52 (1): 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4117840" type="journal article" year="1997">Macqueen &amp; Hernández (1997: 40)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L'Heritier (1788: 30) Bentham" authorityYear="1840" box="[720,884,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[720,884,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The former two are endemic to western 
<collectingCountry box="[1366,1452,374,400]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[144,239,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[250,1336,1116,1998]" captionTargetId="figure-42@3.[241,1346,1107,2006]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Calliandra estebanensis (red dots), C. palmeri (blue squares) and C. longipedicellata (yellow diamonds)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585865" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585865/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figure 3</figureCitation>
) and are clearly segregated geographically with respect to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. M. Hern. A. Branchlet" authorityYear="2019" box="[892,1065,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis box="[892,1065,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. estebanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L'Heritier (1788: 30) Bentham" authorityYear="1840" box="[1290,1451,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[1290,1451,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. grandiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread and morphologically variable species occurring from northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1097,1183,446,472]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1201,1303,446,472]" country="Mexico" name="Durango" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Durango</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1317,1401,446,472]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Sinaloa</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[136,217,482,508]" country="Mexico" name="Sonora" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Sonora</collectingRegion>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[260,369,482,508]" name="Honduras" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Honduras</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[424,556,482,508]" name="El Salvador" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">El Salvador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M." box="[570,912,482,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref3008" refString="Macqueen, D. J. &amp; Hernandez, H. M. (1997) A revision of Calliandra series Racemosae (Leguminosae: Mimosoideae). Kew Bulletin 52 (1): 1 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4117840" type="journal article" year="1997">Macqueen &amp; Hernández 1997</bibRefCitation>
), and is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. M. Hern. A. Branchlet" authorityYear="2019" box="[1179,1353,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Calliandra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estebanensis">
<emphasis box="[1179,1353,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C. estebanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
